cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.OS, cs.AR, cs.CR 

This paper is primarily focused on designing and implementing efficient hash tables on persistent memory, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of persistent memory in operating systems (cs.OS) and mentions the adaptation of two popular hashing schemes, which could fall under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed approach, which could fall under the category of performance analysis (cs.CR).
